      "body" : "That is a label interpreted as account name. The GUI doesn't use accounts, but uses the same database fields for labels. You cannot use both the GUI and accounts in bitcoind interchangably safely..\r\nNote that accounts are deprecated and will be removed in a future release (#3816). \r\n\r\nI do not see how this affects privacy. Both labels and and accounts are not exposed to the outside world.\r\n\r\n(if you don't like the label you can  probably change it under \"receiving addresses\" in the GUI)",
